description.en-US:
It fixes annoying bug in Thunderbird, when composer automatically convert some HTML mails to plain text, discarding all custom formatting. For reference:
<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/557588f82b311f14f89ccccf56a047d564558cf5b87c8d31faf9254adc1e4292/https%3A//bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi%3Fid=414299">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=414299 : Format | Auto-Detect: Messages composed as HTML with &lt;tt&gt; for "fixed width" sections or with simple links get sent as plain text&lt;/tt&gt;</a>&lt;tt&gt; 

<a rel="nofollow" href="https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/1d72ecdeda9e6686432593548690e587882c13eb1b65ce1ff799c33a967bf507/https%3A//getsatisfaction.com/mozilla_messaging/tags/bug_414299">https://getsatisfaction.com/mozilla_messaging/tags/bug_414299</a>

Note: if You use my other extension, <a rel="nofollow" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/thunderbird/addon/stationery/">Stationery</a>, You do not need to install this. Stationery already contain this bug-fix.&lt;/tt&gt;

